node.text:
🍜Have you attempted your own ramen at home? We tried too and made quite a decent one🥰 Decent enough for us to wipe out the noodles and clean the bowl of its broth 🙈⁣
⁣
Ingredients for Ramen Broth:⁣
⁣
❤️2-3 cups prawn/pork broth ( I cooked prawn shells/head, garlic and pork bones in a slow cooker for 8-10 hours) and then strained to get the broth⁣
❤️1 tbsp minced garlic ⁣
❤️1 yellow onion, chopped into fine pieces⁣
❤️2 tbsp shallots oil ⁣
❤️5 pieces shiitake mushrooms, soaked to soften⁣
❤️ 7-8 pieces of dried scallops⁣
❤️1/4 cup milk ⁣
❤️Red chilli flakes (optional)⁣
❤️3 tbsp white/ red Miso paste⁣
❤️2 tbsp chopped chives ⁣
❤️1 tbsp cornflour with 2 tbsp water⁣
⁣
Steps:⁣
1)In a pot, add 2 tbsp shallot oil and fry garlic and onion until fragrant and garlic slightly brown⁣
2)Add prawn/pork broth, dried scallops, mushrooms and let simmer 2-3 mins until onions are soft ⁣
3)Add in milk, miso paste and red chilli flakes and let simmer another 2-3 mins. ⁣
4)Mix cornflour with water and add it to the broth if you want a thicker broth (if not omit this step)⁣
5)Throw in spring onions and stir for 1 min⁣
6)Pour on TOP of cooked Ramen! ⁣
⁣
Probably missing some Japanese essential ingredients but it will do for a quick Ramen fix ❤️ Let me know if you have a recipe that rocks ok! 😘⁣
